&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We want the best staff. You want to make a difference.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic and dynamic Band 6 Registered Midwife who will be caring for women and families and who will provide excellent care at every stage. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;As part of an existing team in East Suffolk, the successful applicant will support and work closely with others to give our clients the best possible care during this exciting time in their lives. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;As part of Better Births, we are committed to providing continuity at every opportunity and would like to welcome midwives who wish to be part of our exciting ventures now and in the future who will provide care and support with passion and integrity.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If you think this may be the opportunity you are looking for please come and see if East Suffolk and North Essex Foundation Trust is the place for you.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;‘&lt;strong&gt;Please note that this role is subject to a DBS check which will be charged to the successful candidate. Full details can be found within the ‘DBS Information’ documents attached to this advert.’&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Marie Fletcher&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Community Maternity Matron&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email: Marie.fletcher@esneft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
